<p>
  {dgettext(
    "help_arcade",
    "The official Quake II demo (1997) — Unit 1 of the singleplayer campaign against the cybernetic Strogg aliens. Fight through interconnected, mission-based levels with the id Tech 2 engine's colored dynamic lighting."
  )}
</p>
<.diagram_arcade_quake2 class="w-full max-w-lg mx-auto my-4" />
<.help_h4 icon={:icon_clock}>{dgettext("help_arcade", "About")}</.help_h4>
<p>
  {dgettext(
    "help_arcade",
    "Released December 9, 1997, developed by a 13-person team at id Software and published by Activision. Quake II shifted from its predecessor's Lovecraftian horror to a sci-fi military campaign against the Strogg — a cybernetic alien race that harvests and assimilates other species. The id Tech 2 engine introduced colored dynamic lighting and a hub-based level structure where you revisit areas with new keys and equipment."
  )}
</p>
<p>
  {dgettext(
    "help_arcade",
    "The demo includes Unit 1 of the singleplayer campaign, featuring mouselook, crouch, and reload mechanics. It entered PC Data's monthly sales chart at #2 for December 1997, behind only Riven. id Software released the full Quake II source code under GPL in 2001. This runs on Yamagi Quake II compiled to WebAssembly."
  )}
</p>
<.help_h4 icon={:icon_send}>{dgettext("help_arcade", "Controls")}</.help_h4>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_arcade", "W / ↑")}</strong> {dgettext("help_arcade", "— Move forward")}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_arcade", "S / ↓")}</strong> {dgettext(
      "help_arcade",
      "— Move backward"
    )}
  </li>
  <li><strong>A</strong> {dgettext("help_arcade", "— Strafe left")}</li>
  <li><strong>D</strong> {dgettext("help_arcade", "— Strafe right")}</li>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_arcade", "Mouse")}</strong> {dgettext("help_arcade", "— Aim / look")}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_arcade", "Left Click")}</strong> {dgettext(
      "help_arcade",
      "— Fire weapon"
    )}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_arcade", "Right Click")}</strong> {dgettext(
      "help_arcade",
      "— Alt-fire"
    )}
  </li>
  <li><strong>E</strong> {dgettext("help_arcade", "— Interact")}</li>
  <li><strong>{dgettext("help_arcade", "Space")}</strong> {dgettext("help_arcade", "— Jump")}</li>
  <li><strong>C</strong> {dgettext("help_arcade", "— Crouch")}</li>
  <li><strong>R</strong> {dgettext("help_arcade", "— Reload")}</li>
  <li><strong>1–9</strong> {dgettext("help_arcade", "— Select weapon")}</li>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_arcade", "Tab")}</strong> {dgettext("help_arcade", "— Inventory")}
  </li>
  <li><strong>{dgettext("help_arcade", "Esc")}</strong> {dgettext("help_arcade", "— Menu")}</li>
</ul>
<.help_h4 icon={:icon_lightbulb}>{dgettext("help_arcade", "Gameplay Tips")}</.help_h4>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_arcade", "Interconnected levels")}</strong>
    {dgettext(
      "help_arcade",
      "— You'll revisit areas with new keys and equipment. Remember the layout."
    )}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_arcade", "Crouch for vents")}</strong>
    {dgettext(
      "help_arcade",
      "— Use crouch to access vents and low passages hiding secrets and shortcuts."
    )}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_arcade", "Weapon effectiveness varies")}</strong>
    {dgettext(
      "help_arcade",
      "— Different weapons are more effective against different Strogg types. Experiment."
    )}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_arcade", "Colored lighting = danger")}</strong>
    {dgettext(
      "help_arcade",
      "— The colored dynamic lighting often signals combat areas and ambushes."
    )}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_arcade", "Reload during quiet moments")}</strong>
    {dgettext("help_arcade", "— Don't get caught in a firefight with an empty magazine.")}
  </li>
</ul>
<.help_h4 icon={:icon_star}>{dgettext("help_arcade", "Did You Know?")}</.help_h4>
<ul>
  <li>
    {dgettext(
      "help_arcade",
      "The name \"Quake II\" was almost \"Wor\" — legal concerns over other title candidates led the team to reuse the Quake name, despite the sequel having zero narrative connection to the original."
    )}
  </li>
  <li>
    {dgettext(
      "help_arcade",
      "id Software released the Quake II source code under GPL in 2001, leading to dozens of enhanced source ports including Yamagi Quake II used here."
    )}
  </li>
  <li>
    {dgettext(
      "help_arcade",
      "This was the last id Software game to feature American McGee, who was fired shortly after its release and went on to create Alice: Madness Returns."
    )}
  </li>
</ul>
<.help_h4 icon={:icon_link}>{dgettext("help_arcade", "See Also")}</.help_h4>
<p>
  <.help_link topic="feature-arcade-quake2">
    {dgettext("help_arcade", "Quake II (Arcade)")}
  </.help_link>
  ·
